-- Taiwanese Stocks: AmTRAN Technology, HTC, Largan, Qisda, Simplo
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2012-07-06T06:00:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-06/taiwanese-stocks-amtran-technology-htc-largan-qisda-simplo.html
Shares of the following companies had
 unusual  moves in Taiwan trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Taipei.  The  Taiex Index (TWSE)  fell 0.3 percent to 7,368.59, capping a 1
percent gain this week.  AmTRAN Technology Co. (2489)  (2489 TT), the maker of Vizio
Televisions, gained 1.3 percent to NT$24.2. The company said
sales rose 37 percent from a year earlier in June.  Ardentec Corp. (3264 TT), a maker of integrated circuit
wafers, added 0.7 percent to NT$21.15. The company said it
signed a seven-year loan with a group of eight banks.  Largan Precision Co. (3008)  (3008 TT), a manufacturer of optical
lens modules, fell 3.3 percent to NT$582. The company said sales
dropped 24 percent from a year earlier in June.  HTC Corp. (2498)  (2498 TT), Asiaâ€™s second-largest smartphone
maker, slid 5.2 percent to NT$322. The company is due to report
second-quarter earnings today. The average of 20 analyst
estimates is for profit of NT$7.97 billion ($267 million).
Citigroup Inc. cut its estimate for HTC shares to NT$250 from
NT$310,  Kevin Chang , an analyst at the bank, wrote in a report.  Qisda Corp. (2352)  (2352 TT), a maker of consumer electronics
products, rose 1.1 percent to NT$7.33. The company said June
sales rose 15 percent from a year earlier.  Simplo Technology Co. (6121)  (6121 TT), a lithium battery
manufacturer, gained 0.7 percent to NT$208. The company said
sales increased 19 percent from a year earlier last month.  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
